# CI-First Preflight Checks

**Green CI is the definition of quality.** Before finalizing any changes, run the appropriate preflight checks to ensure CI will pass.

## Quick Reference: Preflight Commands

### Frontend Changes (webapp or webapp-libs)

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies (if needed)
pnpm install --frozen-lockfile

# 2. Run checks for affected package(s)
pnpm nx run <package-name>:lint
pnpm nx run <package-name>:type-check
pnpm nx run <package-name>:test --watchAll=false

# 3. Build verification (for webapp only)
pnpm nx run webapp:build
```

### Backend Changes (Python/Django)

```bash
# Backend tests run via Docker
pnpm nx run backend:test

# JS/infra linting for backend
pnpm nx run backend:lint:js
```

### Documentation Changes

```bash
pnpm nx run docs:lint
pnpm nx run docs:build
```

